                {
                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px\">Key points</span>",
                    "content": "<ul class=\"key-points\">\n\t<li>Women in lowest-income households spend more time on unpaid work compared to women in highest-income households (39 hours versus 29 hours per week); in contrast, there is little difference in the amount of time men in both lowest-income and highest-income households spend on unpaid work, on average, less than one hour per day. For this reason, the gender gap in time spent on unpaid work is even wider in lowest-income households.</li>\n\t<li>In 2017, for every 100 men living in poor households in the Latin America, there were 113 women in the same situation, a ratio that remained stable over the period 2012\u20142017.</li>\n</ul>\n",
                    "contentActions": [],
                    "creaDate": 1602493918452,
                    "pubDate": 1602493918452,
                    "status": "PUBLISHED",
                    "media": {
