                {
                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px;\">&nbsp;</span>",
                    "content": "<div class=\"methodology\">\n<h1 class=\"methodology-subtitle\">About the data</h1>\n\n<div class=\"methodology-definitions\">\n<h2>Definitions</h2>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><span class=\"concept\">Unpaid work</span>: <span class=\"definition\">in this story refers to work done without payment, which is measured by quantifying the time a person spends on own-use goods production work, unpaid domestic work, unpaid care of household members or unpaid work for other households or for the community and/or volunteer work.<span class=\"footnote-index\">4</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"methodology-coverage\">\n<h2>Coverage</h2>\n\n<p>Women living in six selected countries in Latin America.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"methodology-availability\">\n<h2>Availability</h2>\n\n<p>Data on the six selected countries in Latin America have been provided by the Economic Commission for Latin America and the Caribbean (ECLAC).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n",
